10:T5a5,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"TVSeries","name":"The Melancholy of Haruhi Suzumiya (2009)","description":"Kyon has found himself dragged through many adventures as of late—all because of the SOS Brigade club and its excitable leader, Haruhi Suzumiya. He has stopped believing in the supernatural long ago, but after being forced to join this club based solely on that, he has seen things that cannot be explained logically.<br>\n<br>\nJoining Kyon on his various misadventures is the shy and soft-spoken Mikuru Asahina, the bookish Yuki Nagato, and the ever-cheerful Itsuki Koizumi. Whether it is summer vacation or a school festival, things involving their club and Haruhi herself always end up becoming strange.<br>\n<br>\n<i>Note:  This is a re-airing of the original Suzumiya Haruhi no Yuuutsu series, taken from the DVD release and aired in chronological order, adding 14 additional episodes with new content. These new episodes are episodes 8 (Bamboo Leaf Rhapsody), 12-19 (Endless Eight), and 20-24 (The Sigh of Suzumiya Haruhi Parts 1-5).","image":"https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx4382-ojMWjGFfJFmN.png","datePublished":"2009-04-03","numberOfEpisodes":28,"countryOfOrigin":"JP","inLanguage":"ja","genre":["Comedy","Mystery","Sci-Fi","Slice of Life","Supernatural"],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":7.1,"bestRating":10,"ratingCount":0}}5:[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$10"}}],["$","$L11",null,{"initialDrama":{"id":"b85fcf42-9752-4186-a080-d6106f9124b6","tmdb_id":4382,"imdb_id":null,"content_type":"anime","title":"The Melancholy of Haruhi Suzumiya (2009)","original_title":"涼宮ハルヒの憂鬱","overview":"Kyon has found himself dragged through many adventures as of late—all because of the SOS Brigade club and its excitable leader, Haruhi Suzumiya. He has stopped believing in the supernatural long ago, but after being forced to join this club based solely on that, he has seen things that cannot be explained logically.<br>\n<br>\nJoining Kyon on his various misadventures is the shy and soft-spoken Mikuru Asahina, the bookish Yuki Nagato, and the ever-cheerful Itsuki Koizumi. Whether it is summer vacation or a school festival, things involving their club and Haruhi herself always end up becoming strange.<br>\n<br>\n<i>Note:  This is a re-airing of the original Suzumiya Haruhi no Yuuutsu series, taken from the DVD release and aired in chronological order, adding 14 additional episodes with new content. These new episodes are episodes 8 (Bamboo Leaf Rhapsody), 12-19 (Endless Eight), and 20-24 (The Sigh of Suzumiya Haruhi Parts 1-5).","poster_path":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/cover/large/bx4382-ojMWjGFfJFmN.png","backdrop_path":"https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/anime/banner/4382-KDWzcDSH9H07.jpg","release_date":null,"first_air_date":"2009-04-03","status":"published","original_language":"ja","origin_country":["JP"],"genres":[{"id":1,"name":"Comedy"},{"id":2,"name":"Mystery"},{"id":3,"name":"Sci-Fi"},{"id":4,"name":"Slice of Life"},{"id":5,"name":"Supernatural"}],"popularity":114602,"vote_average":7.1,"vote_count":null,"runtime":24,"number_of_seasons":null,"number_of_episodes":28,"created_at":"2026-05-02T08:50:01.546508+00:00","updated_at":"2026-05-02T08:50:01.503+00:00","tagline":null,"homepage":null,"budget":null,"revenue":null,"production_companies":[{"name":"Kyoto Animation"}],"production_countries":null,"spoken_languages":null,"networks":[],"last_air_date":"2009-10-09","in_production":false,"tmdb_status":"Ended","content_rating":null,"keywords":[{"id":1,"name":"Primarily Teen Cast"},{"id":2,"name":"Female Protagonist"},{"id":3,"name":"School"},{"id":4,"name":"Urban Fantasy"},{"id":5,"name":"School Club"},{"id":6,"name":"Time Manipulation"},{"id":7,"name":"Gods"},{"id":8,"name":"Aliens"},{"id":9,"name":"Male Protagonist"},{"id":10,"name":"Parody"},{"id":11,"name"